  "text": "Aside from bacterial strains isolated from potato rhizosphere in this study, P. atrosepticum strain SM1 (Kindly provided from Islamic Azad University-Science and Research Branch, Iran) was used as the source of naturally produced AHL molecules. Chromobacterium violaceum CV026 [CITATION_1] (provided by Vittorio Venturi, ICEGB, Area Science park, Italy) and Agrobacterium tumefaciens NT1 [CITATION_2] ) (provided by Yves Dessaux, CNRS, Gif-sur-Yvette, France) were used as the indicator strains for AHLs detection.",
